{
  "texts": [
    "Thus CTRLSum differs from other controllable summarization methods in not requiring separate models for each control aspect, generalizing to new keywords at test time.",
    "We use the pre-trained CTRLSum model foot_4 in three scenarios: GOLD, PRED and ZERO.",
    "For GOLD we use the 3 most frequently mentioned gold salient entities in each document foot_5 as \"keywords\" (all unique mentions of these entities are used, excluding pronouns); in PRED we generate predicted salient entities using GPT-4 (OpenAI 2023), a generative LLM that achieves humanlevel performance on a range of benchmarks, using the prompt 'Find the top 3 salient entities in the following document.",
    "', and in ZERO we test without adding salient entities.",
    "GPT-4 GPT-4 (OpenAI, 2023) is the latest version of Generative Pre-trained Transformers at the time of writing."
  ]
}